Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_contex..._clock_mapping(25.10)    timing_contex..._clock_mapping(25.10)

Name
       timing_context_port_based_clock_mapping

Syntax
       timing_context_port_based_clock_mapping {true | false}

       Default: false

       Enables clock mapping based on block ports.

       When set to true, clock mapping is done depending solely on clock prop-
       erty  of  the  top  and  block clock for each clock and data port sepa-
       rately. For enabling N-to-1 or 1-to-N clock mapping, this global  vari-
       able should be set true.

       When  set  to  false, only 1-to-1 clock mapping is done. In such cases,
       the following rules are used to determine clock mapping:

              * Rule1: Clocks with matching property (period/duty cycle)

              * Rule2: Clocks with matching name

              * Rule3: Clocks present on maximum number common ports

              * Rule4: Any one of the matching clocks

       For example,

              *

                Consider the following illustration:

                When  set  to  true,  the  following  mapping  will  be  seen:
                ________________________________________________________

                | Block Port      |  Block Clock     |  Mapped top      |

                |                 |                  |   clock          |

                |_________________|__________________|__________________|

                | P1              |  CLK             |  CLK, TCLK       |

                |_________________|__________________|__________________|

                When set to false, CLK will be mapped to CLK according to Rule
                2.

       Notes:

              * The  context_data  property of block port can be accessed only
                when this global variable is set true.

              * When set to true, the software may increase the  pessimism  as
                the  worst  latency/arrival  will  be picked for block context
                analysis.

              * If there are multiple block clocks that can be mapped to  same
                top clock on the same block port, then Tempus does not perform
                auto  mapping  (when  set to true). Whereas for the false set-
                ting, clock mapping is done depending on the  above  mentioned
                rules.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

